 A 19-year-old learner from the Royal Academy, in Queenstown, who went missing on the 14th of March, was found unconscious on Friday. According to police spokesperson, Captain Namhla Mdleleni, the boy, Siphesande Nogela, was found by members of Red Guard Security near Uitsig Farm on Friday morning. “He was found unconscious and was taken to Frontier Hospital for medical examination,” she said. Queenstown Cluster Commander, Major General Funeka Siganga, commended the members for the assistance. 